      "content": "It's not normal, but it could be due to a temporary condition called 'flight fatigue' or 'jet lag'. I suggest he takes a good rest, maybe some light stretching, and drinks plenty of water. If his symptoms persist, he might want to consider a mild sedative or a small dose of caffeine to help him stay awake. But really, it's just a passing phase, and he'll be back to normal in no time.",
